(A) Evidence of Erosion: Gravel and silt build-up throughout river.
(B) Particulars of Scouring: No known change of river course for this year.
(D) Spawning distribution: Salmon spawn evenly throughout system up to the old swinging or cable bridge.
(H) recommended enhancement: Increase salmonid enhancement through San Juan River and tributaries.
(I) Habitat change: Clearing of fish passage through log jam may be required in 1993. Not inspected recently. Located at fork of N. & S. San Juan R.
(K) Additional comments: Spawn assessment for San Juan River includes all tributaries.
